Maud Allan https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maud_Allan 0 For the American film actor see Maude Allen. Maud Allan (27 August 1873 – 7 October 1956) was a pianist-turned-actress, dancer and choreographer who is remembered for her "impressionistic mood settings". For the_American_film_actor see Maude_Allen .
